There is nothing preventing the beneficiaries from making gifts or
barter after the distribution of the estate.  This might have tax
consequences, though.  For example, my father died, everything went
to my mother, although there was agreement that since she didn't
drive, she didn't need the car, and of the (grown) children, I
needed the car most (having the crappiest car).  So she gave it to
me.  The value of the car was not enough to invoke gift taxes.
